The paper describes a technique for autonomous underwater robots to track and reidentify human divers in real time, which involves computer vision and machine learning algorithms. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of a custom CNN for realtime diver detection, which suggests that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms for tracking and reidentification, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses practical considerations for applying multi-person tracking to on-board autonomous robot operations, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of videos, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
